<p>
Ah, yes, mostly music. We have a Yamaha YDP-113
piano which is finally getting played, yay me (and
yay W-'s decision to get it about two decades
ago). I want to get the hang of at least Simply
Sing's intermediate lessons so I can finally play
those Disney songs at a consistent tempo, which
means A+ will be able to sing instead of having to
stop and restart as I stumble on notes. Plus music
has a way of gently pointing out when my attention
wanders, so there's that. This feels like a
reasonably good use of my time.
</p>
